<br>
There are already plenty of class boards where people suggest ideas. There are feedback areas at SoE sites.  There are guild sites that take feedback.  There is in game feedback.  In short, there are PLENTY of feedback mechanisms.  <br>
<br>
Now that SoE is more open to ideas, they have a veritable treasure trove of information at their fingertips.  They don't need another, lowly populated, highly restrictive site to cull ideas when they already have mountains of good info from their highly responsive player base.<br>
<br>
Sorry to rain on the parade.  <br>
<br>
I would suggest you contact an active board (whether general or class based) and try to become a moderator or contributor.  The communities get lots of value from active moderators and posters...<br>
